          "question_format": "mcq",
          "question": "Find the gradient of the tangent to the curve $y = 2^x + 2^{-x}$ at the point $(2, \\frac{17}{4})$.",
          "options": [
            "$\\frac{15}{4}\\ln 2$",
            "$\\frac{17}{4}\\ln 2$",
            "$\\frac{17}{16}\\ln 2$",
            "$\\frac{15}{16}\\ln 2$"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "$\\frac{dy}{dx} = (2^x - 2^{-x})\\ln 2$. At $x=2$: $(4 - \\frac{1}{4})\\ln 2 = \\frac{15}{4}\\ln 2$.",
