        {
          "question_format": "mcq",
          "question": "The population of Cambridge is modelled by $P = P_0 k^t$, where $P = 37000$ when $t=0$ and $P = 109000$ when $t=100$. Which expression gives $\\frac{dP}{dt}$ in the year 2000?",
          "options": [
            "$109000\\ln\\!\\left(\\left(\\frac{109000}{37000}\\right)^{1/100}\\right)$",
            "$37000\\ln\\!\\left(\\left(\\frac{109000}{37000}\\right)^{1/100}\\right)$",
            "$109000\\left(\\frac{109000}{37000}\\right)^{1/100}$",
            "$\\ln(109000) - \\ln(37000)$"
          ],
          "correct_option": "A",
          "explanation": "$\\frac{dP}{dt} = P_0 k^t \\ln k = P \\ln k$. In 2000, $t=100$ so $P=109000$ and $k = \\left(\\frac{109000}{37000}\\right)^{1/100}$.",
          "diagram_required": "none"
